WEBVTT

00:36.790 --> 00:38.340
Let me ask you one thing

00:38.340 --> 00:39.930
because this might be my last chance.

00:41.280 --> 00:43.040
When I kissed you without your permission...

00:43.040 --> 00:44.210
Can you not bring that up until...

00:44.210 --> 00:45.490
What should I do?

00:48.340 --> 00:49.680
Do you want me to apologize?

00:52.020 --> 00:53.830
Or confess?

01:04.150 --> 01:07.580
You're quite charming.

01:10.950 --> 01:12.840
You're charming, but you live dangerously.

01:14.090 --> 01:15.890
I don't like danger,

01:17.870 --> 01:20.620
but every time I look at you, I fall for you.

01:21.830 --> 01:23.420
I'm sorry, but I have to stand you up this time.

01:25.470 --> 01:26.380
Leave?

01:30.460 --> 01:32.009
Did something happen?

01:32.450 --> 01:33.850
I think I have to go now.

01:33.850 --> 01:34.940
Now?

01:34.940 --> 01:35.880
I'm sorry.

01:37.900 --> 01:40.700
Because of regulations, I can't...

01:41.150 --> 01:42.100
Was he a fellow soldier?

01:42.280 --> 01:43.220
Yes, he was.

01:43.930 --> 01:45.610
That means that if you...

01:45.610 --> 01:46.440
That means...

01:46.440 --> 01:48.289
So…

01:51.110 --> 01:52.650
Let's not talk about that.

01:55.950 --> 01:58.110
I wanted to have more time.

01:59.550 --> 02:03.570
So I could clear my head and get rid of my fear

02:05.170 --> 02:07.400
to become a girlfriend of

02:07.400 --> 02:11.190
this charming yet dangerous guy.

02:11.190 --> 02:12.920
I need time to think about it.

02:15.930 --> 02:21.140
But you left me a lot.

02:22.060 --> 02:24.640
I can't get mad at you.

02:25.060 --> 02:27.450
I can't even beg you to stay with me.

02:29.930 --> 02:32.320
I feel like I'm an idiot for wanting you.

02:34.370 --> 02:41.270
I feel a little resentful toward you.

02:43.310 --> 02:45.070
Apologize to me.

02:45.070 --> 02:46.600
I'll accept it.

02:55.430 --> 02:56.660
I'm sorry.

02:57.250 --> 02:58.950
I want you to take care of yourself.

03:01.360 --> 03:03.910
Ma'am.

03:56.410 --> 04:02.270
One, two, three, four.

04:02.270 --> 04:05.120
One, two, three, four!

04:05.120 --> 04:06.670
One, two, three, four!

04:06.670 --> 04:09.450
There are so many

04:09.450 --> 04:12.450
cool guys

04:12.450 --> 04:15.550
I'm that guy

04:15.550 --> 04:18.610
I'm the coolest guy

04:21.399 --> 04:22.270
Hello.

04:22.820 --> 04:24.920
Where's Captain Yoo?

04:24.920 --> 04:26.580
He's not in his office.

04:26.580 --> 04:29.460
He left last night.

04:29.460 --> 04:32.000
He's taking a commercial jet.

04:32.450 --> 04:34.820
He's probably on the plane as we speak.

04:35.990 --> 04:37.090
Ma'am.

04:43.030 --> 04:45.610
Wow! He's cold.

05:05.710 --> 05:10.690
They still have this picture. Father!

05:12.560 --> 05:13.540
Like your mother said,

05:13.540 --> 05:15.720
you should've become a judge.

05:16.100 --> 05:18.500
No one respects soldiers these days.

05:20.550 --> 05:22.260
I'm not only smart,

05:22.260 --> 05:23.900
but I'm athletic as well.

05:23.900 --> 05:25.320
Becoming a judge would be a waste of my talents.

05:26.820 --> 05:30.140
I want you to live a long and healthy life.

05:30.900 --> 05:33.420
I'll let you take a picture with your general son.

05:35.050 --> 05:38.480
Who's going to make you someone with no background, a general?

05:38.480 --> 05:40.150
You couldn't get promoted to major.

05:40.150 --> 05:41.820
So arrogant you are.

05:43.710 --> 05:44.790
Are you okay?

05:44.790 --> 05:46.440
I did what you've taught me.

05:47.450 --> 05:48.800
Please be proud of me.

05:48.800 --> 05:56.000
There are times that going to jail is more honorable
than being promoted as a soldier.

05:56.630 --> 05:58.240
Good job!

05:59.650 --> 06:02.190
It's ready. Come on in.

06:04.460 --> 06:06.720
Go ahead. I'll bring mother along.

06:07.220 --> 06:08.270
Okay.

06:16.880 --> 06:20.920
Here we go. One, two, three!

06:25.160 --> 06:28.090
Trainee Number 17! Ready to descend!

06:28.090 --> 06:29.540
Descend!

06:38.380 --> 06:41.520
Help! Please help me!

06:45.290 --> 06:47.720
Down! Up!

06:47.720 --> 06:50.430
Up!Down!

06:50.430 --> 06:55.900
On your stomachs! One, two! Stand up!

06:56.340 --> 06:57.280
It's not a physical thing.

06:57.280 --> 06:58.600
Is it your brain, then?

06:58.600 --> 06:59.780
No, sir!

06:59.780 --> 07:00.560
Change!

07:00.560 --> 07:02.200
Change!

07:10.300 --> 07:11.670
Do you want to kill me?

07:11.670 --> 07:13.000
Yes, sir!

07:13.000 --> 07:14.680
You're not strong enough.

07:14.680 --> 07:17.160
Touch the gate and come back. 30 seconds.

07:17.160 --> 07:18.000
Turn left!

07:19.670 --> 07:21.130
If you meet me outside,

07:21.130 --> 07:23.320
go ahead and beat me up.

07:23.320 --> 07:27.410
You need to be strong to do that. Ready! Run!

07:31.450 --> 07:35.790
A really handsome trainee is ready to descend!

07:36.000 --> 07:37.210
Descend!

07:44.480 --> 07:45.810
Down!

07:56.200 --> 07:58.630
Trainee, stop fooling around and come down.

08:01.180 --> 08:02.320
Watch and learn!

08:02.320 --> 08:04.120
That's how you repel head first.

08:16.480 --> 08:18.170
What are you doing here on your leave?

08:18.560 --> 08:20.010
I missed you a lot.

08:20.620 --> 08:22.030
When do you finish?

08:22.320 --> 08:25.150
Wrap this up quickly and let's have a drink.

08:27.740 --> 08:29.450
How was your father's retirement ceremony?

08:29.790 --> 08:31.950
I almost cried when I gave him flowers.

08:32.530 --> 08:35.440
I'm glad you're back safe and sound, sir!

08:35.809 --> 08:36.640
Thank you.

08:40.200 --> 08:41.159
It's been a year

08:41.159 --> 08:43.140
since we all got together, right?

08:43.530 --> 08:47.670
Let's get a box of arrack and drink it from beer glasses.

08:47.670 --> 08:48.810
A beer glass?

08:49.340 --> 08:52.240
Yes, let's drink it until one of us dies.

08:52.590 --> 08:53.780
Do you know them?

08:53.780 --> 08:56.140
I was their instructor during Hell Week.

08:56.470 --> 08:57.510
Right!

08:57.510 --> 08:58.450
It's okay.

08:59.830 --> 09:01.510
Who would think I'm a soldier?

09:02.290 --> 09:04.990
Don't put your collar up. You look like a soldier.

09:04.990 --> 09:07.410
Sergeant Seo?

09:09.510 --> 09:11.970
Hello, Sergeant Seo Dae Young?

09:12.730 --> 09:14.010
Your cover has been blown.

09:15.260 --> 09:16.540
Can we secure a path of retreat?

09:17.850 --> 09:20.250
At five o'clock.

09:20.960 --> 09:24.090
Hello. Sergeant Seo Dae Young, instructor from hell.

09:25.150 --> 09:26.520
Do you remember me?

09:28.090 --> 09:31.760
You promised us whenever you gave us a hard time

09:31.760 --> 09:35.170
if we bumped into you outside,

09:35.450 --> 09:37.010
we could beat you up.

09:37.960 --> 09:39.270
I said "outside."

09:39.270 --> 09:40.580
This isn't outside. This is inside.

09:41.120 --> 09:43.000
Beside, let me have a drink first.

09:45.530 --> 09:47.670
You guys! Give him a break.

09:48.830 --> 09:52.220
Just keep it as a fond memory and move on.

09:53.850 --> 09:55.780
A fond memory?

09:55.780 --> 09:58.050
On the count of three. One!

09:58.050 --> 09:58.860
Three!

10:12.810 --> 10:14.480
Is today Armed Forces Day or something?

10:15.180 --> 10:16.290
Hey! Get them!

10:19.880 --> 10:21.370
At two o'clock! Three!

10:21.930 --> 10:23.420
No! No!

10:51.390 --> 10:52.180
Where did they go?

11:24.860 --> 11:26.590
Stop! Stop!

11:26.590 --> 11:28.300
Get them! Go get them!

11:28.300 --> 11:29.830
That way! That way!

11:31.260 --> 11:32.360
Quick!

11:43.510 --> 11:44.530
That way! That way!

11:45.310 --> 11:47.010
Alley! That alley there!

11:52.870 --> 11:54.620
You have a funny way of counting.

11:54.950 --> 11:56.290
How does three come after one?

11:57.130 --> 11:58.600
I'm only good at sports.

11:58.600 --> 12:00.690
Why don't you, a smart guy, count next time?

12:01.400 --> 12:03.240
I can't breathe. Geez!

12:05.830 --> 12:06.780
The instructor from hell

12:06.780 --> 12:08.440
can't live up to his reputation anymore.

12:08.910 --> 12:12.300
Wait a minute! I need to beat you up too.

12:13.490 --> 12:15.270
When I was in the Army Academy,

12:15.270 --> 12:17.270
you tormented me a lot. Don't you remember?

12:17.270 --> 12:20.100
Yes, I do. Do you want to beat me up now?

12:23.310 --> 12:24.540
Actually, I don't remember.

12:24.990 --> 12:27.110
I only have happy memories about you.

12:28.500 --> 12:29.500
Wow! I'm sober now.

12:33.630 --> 12:36.140
Did you drink the wine I left?

12:36.610 --> 12:37.990
I tasted it, yes.

12:37.990 --> 12:39.730
Did you drink it alone?

12:39.730 --> 12:41.170
With Dr. Kang.

12:43.050 --> 12:44.060
Any progress?

12:44.480 --> 12:45.390
Not really.

12:46.740 --> 12:49.180
I feel like I'm being dumped

12:49.180 --> 12:50.330
every time I leave.

12:53.900 --> 12:55.340
I still have feelings for her,

12:56.820 --> 12:58.270
but it'll get better as time goes by.

12:59.240 --> 13:01.890
If you keep trying, she'll eventually accept you.

13:01.890 --> 13:03.260
I can't believe what I'm hearing right now.

13:03.260 --> 13:05.250
You're in no position to give me advice.

13:05.250 --> 13:06.610
It's not that I don't want to be with her.

13:07.250 --> 13:09.250
Actully, I am.

13:09.690 --> 13:11.680
It hurts when departing from her.

13:14.190 --> 13:15.640
We're so pathetic.

13:17.030 --> 13:17.950
Hanging out with each other

13:17.950 --> 13:19.580
doesn't help the situation.

13:24.240 --> 13:25.480
If you'll excuse me.

13:26.810 --> 13:27.810
Where are you going?

13:27.810 --> 13:30.860
I'm going home. This is my neighborhood.

13:37.470 --> 13:39.110
Is that why you came this way?

13:40.210 --> 13:41.570
This is how you save on taxi fare?

13:41.570 --> 13:43.580
Enjoy the rest of your leave, sir!

13:47.480 --> 13:49.560
You're not going to offer me some instant noodles?

13:49.560 --> 13:51.330
This is your neighborhood.

14:21.620 --> 14:24.620
Hello? Hello?

14:26.160 --> 14:28.350
Seo Dae Young! Is that really you?

14:31.680 --> 14:32.950
You answered the phone.

14:35.280 --> 14:36.430
Why?

14:36.630 --> 14:37.720
Is there a problem?

14:42.570 --> 14:45.000
Talk to me. You answered the phone, right?

14:48.340 --> 14:49.490
No.

14:50.510 --> 14:52.670
Just listen to me.

14:53.250 --> 14:56.760
Don't hang up, okay?

14:59.530 --> 15:01.660
I'm doing well.

15:01.660 --> 15:03.630
I'm in my combat uniform

15:03.630 --> 15:05.990
and I haven't gotten any mosquito bites.

15:06.210 --> 15:08.880
I'm doing really well in a foreign land

15:09.220 --> 15:11.120
and I miss Seo Dae Young like crazy.

15:14.840 --> 15:16.140
Have you seen Shi Jin?

15:16.760 --> 15:19.170
He was really mean to me while he was here.

15:19.170 --> 15:22.200
He's like, "What do you see in Seo Dae Young
to make you come all the way here?"

15:22.200 --> 15:23.700
He said he liked the way I try

15:23.700 --> 15:25.630
to keep this relationship going.

15:27.970 --> 15:30.840
You know what? I don't mind doing this.

15:31.670 --> 15:34.820
When I think about the way you loved me.

16:07.240 --> 16:08.370
Are you listening to me?

16:11.520 --> 16:14.300
If you are, can you at least make a breathing sound?

16:24.630 --> 16:27.320
You're coming home, right?

16:27.320 --> 16:29.390
I can't wait. I got some really good wine for you.

16:29.390 --> 16:31.170
I won't drink with only a girl.

16:31.450 --> 16:32.810
Get a guy for me.

16:33.010 --> 16:34.410
A good one.

16:34.940 --> 16:36.610
What about the guy you bumped into again?

16:37.140 --> 16:38.350
He's not your type?

16:46.790 --> 16:49.780
Actually, he's the best.

16:51.910 --> 16:53.470
I shouldn't have accepted his apology.

16:54.060 --> 16:58.960
I should've gone to him

17:02.610 --> 17:06.390
and confessed how I really felt.

17:06.390 --> 17:10.790
He must be very disappointed in me.

18:03.370 --> 18:04.730
Dame it.

18:24.440 --> 18:25.660
Stop.

18:58.290 --> 18:59.590
There.

19:20.080 --> 19:22.050
Can you translate for me?

19:22.050 --> 19:25.520
If you suck on this, it'll make your stomach hurt.

19:25.930 --> 19:27.850
Don't suck on this thing from now on.

19:28.040 --> 19:31.150
Can you promise me?

19:32.210 --> 19:35.520
If you suck on something like this, I'll shoot you.

19:41.330 --> 19:44.470
You need to wash your hands before eating.

19:46.350 --> 19:52.290
If you don't wash your hands before eating, I'll shoot you.

20:00.130 --> 20:01.220
Why are they laughing?

20:01.690 --> 20:03.140
Did you say something silly to them?

20:04.850 --> 20:05.720
They’re in the age that even small things can make them laugh.

20:30.330 --> 20:31.620
Sir!

20:32.060 --> 20:33.650
Sergeant Seo, where are you now?

20:34.160 --> 20:35.000
I'm in my office.

20:35.000 --> 20:37.230
I'm fishing in Yangpyeong.

20:39.020 --> 20:40.880
The scenery's beautiful and the water's clean.

20:40.880 --> 20:42.640
It’s such a pleasant place.

20:43.240 --> 20:44.790
Why did you call me?

20:46.880 --> 20:48.260
I'm bored.

20:49.400 --> 20:50.980
Can you come join me?

20:52.040 --> 20:54.380
It's quite scary at night here.

20:54.700 --> 20:55.550
Bye.

21:07.210 --> 21:08.320
Sergeant Seo, I'm in big trouble.

21:36.940 --> 21:38.100
I don't operate anymore.

21:38.840 --> 21:40.910
Operating skills aren't helping my career at all.

21:42.240 --> 21:45.290
I'm going home soon and when I go back,

21:45.290 --> 21:47.850
I have to get back up to where I was.

21:47.900 --> 21:48.960
I'm busy.

21:51.290 --> 21:52.940
Right.

21:59.160 --> 22:00.190
Here.

22:05.650 --> 22:07.760
You'll come back here before me anyway.

22:10.840 --> 22:15.340
Why don't you find out if you really come back?

23:14.540 --> 23:15.790
No way!

23:16.630 --> 23:17.670
Yes. This is the same car.

23:18.440 --> 23:20.580
You're too good to be a doctor.

23:21.660 --> 23:23.680
That's why I make more money at the hardware store.

23:25.300 --> 23:26.810
I heard you were leaving today.

23:27.300 --> 23:30.100
Yes. Thank you for everything.

23:31.850 --> 23:34.020
This won't cover all the costs,

23:34.020 --> 23:36.040
but I want you to take it.

23:36.450 --> 23:38.040
If you insist,

23:40.030 --> 23:42.320
how about paying 10 dollars a month for a long time?

23:45.100 --> 23:46.360
Good.

23:46.360 --> 23:47.750
I'll pay you off bit by bit.

23:48.290 --> 23:49.320
Thank you.

23:49.640 --> 23:50.830
Best wishes.

23:50.830 --> 23:52.910
If you want to do something rewarding, come back.

23:54.610 --> 23:57.510
Volunteer work, rescue missions.

23:58.180 --> 24:00.290
I think I've done my fair share of volunteer work.

24:01.270 --> 24:02.890
I need to go back to where I belong.

24:04.110 --> 24:06.640
How much longer are you going to stay here?

24:07.410 --> 24:10.470
This is the last year of my sabbatical leave.

24:10.470 --> 24:11.420
Who knows? I can't even keep the plan

24:11.420 --> 24:13.790
that I made for the day sometimes.

24:14.380 --> 24:15.420
Have a safe trip home.

24:16.520 --> 24:17.500
Take care of yourself.

24:18.180 --> 24:19.690
Please say hi to Ye Hwa for me.

24:52.780 --> 24:54.320
Everybody's waiting. What are you doing here?

24:55.920 --> 24:56.980
I'll be over in five minutes.

24:56.980 --> 24:58.650
Why didn't you start five minutes earlier?

25:01.600 --> 25:03.680
Hepatamine, preamine...

25:03.680 --> 25:05.100
Since we're not going to see each other again,

25:05.100 --> 25:06.180
can I ask you something?

25:06.180 --> 25:07.050
No.

25:08.070 --> 25:10.150
Let me see. The IV box is...

25:10.310 --> 25:12.210
Do you have feelings for Shi Jin?

25:17.200 --> 25:19.000
I get it, loud and clear.

25:19.530 --> 25:20.480
Thank you.

25:21.240 --> 25:23.790
What do you mean? I didn't say anything.

25:24.320 --> 25:26.370
You did. With your body.

25:27.560 --> 25:28.470
Excuse me.

25:31.360 --> 25:33.070
Speaking of the devil, it's Shi Jin.

25:34.300 --> 25:35.810
I'm glad you called.

25:35.810 --> 25:37.580
Ms. Kang Mo Yeon. Dr. Kang Mo Yeon.

25:37.580 --> 25:39.100
Kang Mo Yeon.

25:39.100 --> 25:40.430
I don't know how to address her

25:40.430 --> 25:41.960
before I figure out your relationship.

25:42.620 --> 25:44.290
But does she like you?

25:44.590 --> 25:45.770
Hey, Yoon Myung Joo!

25:51.320 --> 25:53.860
You didn't even give me your official rank and name?

25:54.290 --> 25:55.960
Who are you calling me as?

25:55.960 --> 25:57.920
A friend? Your superior?

25:57.920 --> 25:59.210
You brother next door.

25:59.740 --> 26:01.370
I'm having coffee with Sergeant Seo.

26:02.450 --> 26:03.710
I'm having a latte

26:04.430 --> 26:06.340
and he's having an espresso.

26:07.040 --> 26:09.320
I don't know if he even knows what he's drinking.

26:10.530 --> 26:11.540
He knows.

26:12.800 --> 26:14.020
I told him.

26:17.990 --> 26:19.130
By the way, what was that all about?

26:19.580 --> 26:21.910
I said it so you'd sweat a little.

26:22.860 --> 26:24.940
I'm in a battle of nerves

26:24.940 --> 26:26.160
with an acquaintance called Kang Mo Yeon.

26:26.160 --> 26:27.550
An acquaintance?

26:29.040 --> 26:31.130
Why are you harassing a civilian?

26:31.330 --> 26:33.720
You avoided the subject.

26:34.070 --> 26:35.880
Are you curious about how she reacted?

26:36.630 --> 26:38.370
Hang up!

26:39.180 --> 26:40.190
How is she?

26:41.330 --> 26:42.140
Angry?

26:42.140 --> 26:43.480
She's angry,

26:43.480 --> 26:44.410
but she's quite pretty

26:44.410 --> 26:45.810
even in anger.

26:47.840 --> 26:48.840
Keep up the good work.

26:49.580 --> 26:50.730
Bye.

26:51.000 --> 26:51.790
Sir!

26:53.520 --> 26:55.510
He didn't ask me to put you on the phone.

26:56.450 --> 26:57.510
I guess I caught him off guard.

26:57.510 --> 26:58.830
Of course.

26:59.030 --> 26:59.990
He wouldn't just forget

26:59.990 --> 27:01.640
a pretty face like me that quickly.

27:04.360 --> 27:05.900
Is this why he likes you?

27:05.900 --> 27:07.920
Medical team! Medical team!

27:09.830 --> 27:12.650
Let's take a picture.

27:14.910 --> 27:17.480
Go take some pictures. That's why you're here.

27:17.480 --> 27:18.490
Mo Yeon!

27:18.790 --> 27:19.690
Coming!

27:22.110 --> 27:23.580
You're right,

27:23.910 --> 27:25.310
but that's not the only thing we came here for.

27:26.390 --> 27:28.510
I couldn't finish it because you interrupted me.

27:28.960 --> 27:30.980
Check the list of medicines

27:30.980 --> 27:33.040
and make sure the transfer to the UN goes smoothly.

27:33.420 --> 27:37.170
Take care until you return home.

27:45.460 --> 27:48.590
-Let's go home! - Let's go home!

27:50.090 --> 27:54.020
Here we go! One, two, three!

28:00.610 --> 28:01.620
Good.

28:01.620 --> 28:03.640
Thank you for everything.

28:03.640 --> 28:05.390
Thank you all.

28:08.340 --> 28:10.390
To show his appreciation, our commander

28:10.390 --> 28:11.370
has commanded us

28:11.370 --> 28:12.590
to take you to the airport by chopper.

28:17.910 --> 28:20.260
We don't have to take a bus for four hours?

28:20.260 --> 28:22.030
We'll take you to the Uruk International Airport

28:22.030 --> 28:23.870
safely in half an hour.

28:23.870 --> 28:25.580
Wow.

28:28.090 --> 28:31.100
We can't take you all at once so half of you will...

28:31.100 --> 28:32.640
Rock, paper, scissors.

28:44.670 --> 28:46.740
Rock, paper, scissors. No cheating!

28:51.650 --> 28:56.030
Wow! So beautiful and so cool!

28:56.760 --> 28:59.890
It's too bad I can't enjoy this more.

29:00.390 --> 29:02.160
Look at the color of the water.

29:02.160 --> 29:05.060
We should be enjoying something like this

29:05.420 --> 29:07.610
instead of being stuck in the OR

29:07.610 --> 29:13.010
and looking at internal organs the large intestine, and the small intestine.

29:13.010 --> 29:15.650
Like Captain Yoo always said

29:15.870 --> 29:18.700
the beautiful scenes make him want to protect this country.

30:53.270 --> 30:54.370
Stop fooling around.

31:03.580 --> 31:07.180
How handsome! When I go back to Korea...

31:08.720 --> 31:09.940
Geez! Mr. Koh!

31:09.940 --> 31:11.950
You sleepyhead!

31:12.950 --> 31:16.030
Put your helmet on. Don't forget your helmet.

31:16.030 --> 31:18.980
You have to wear a helmet at all times!

31:19.560 --> 31:21.400
You're ruining my hair.

31:23.360 --> 31:27.170
If your skull breaks, you're going to die.

31:40.400 --> 31:41.960
Where are the plates?

32:00.110 --> 32:01.200
Earthquake! Run!

33:06.650 --> 33:09.250
Earthquake! Get out of here!

33:09.250 --> 33:11.550
You idiot! Let's get out of here!

33:37.140 --> 33:39.010
Mr. Koh.

34:08.719 --> 34:11.780
What... what is going on?

34:36.199 --> 34:38.190
Communication security of the Commander's office...

34:38.190 --> 34:39.920
This is Captain Yoo Shi Jin from Alpha Team.

34:40.760 --> 34:43.230
Put anyone who knows the situation in Mouru through.

34:44.010 --> 34:45.239
Don't hang up and do it now!

34:57.780 --> 35:00.110
Yes. The medical services team is coming home today,

35:00.110 --> 35:02.170
but we can't get hold of them.

35:02.170 --> 35:04.850
Yes, sir.

35:05.050 --> 35:06.000
The earthquake started in Mouru,

35:06.000 --> 35:07.930
2,000 kilometers away

35:07.930 --> 35:10.000
from the capital of Uruk.

35:12.950 --> 35:15.240
No! Oh my!

35:15.240 --> 35:16.930
What happened to Chi Hoon?

35:16.930 --> 35:18.770
It's okay.

35:19.290 --> 35:20.450
Everything will be fine.

35:20.820 --> 35:22.460
What do I know?

35:22.460 --> 35:24.610
I just saw the news.

35:24.610 --> 35:26.060
I'm on my way to an emergency meeting.

35:26.060 --> 35:27.650
I'll let you know as soon as I find out anything.

35:33.430 --> 35:34.830
We contacted headquarters,

35:34.830 --> 35:35.880
but we can't locate Lieutenant Yoon Myung Joo

35:35.880 --> 35:38.600
who's in Mouru at the moment, so...

35:38.600 --> 35:40.080
What about the planes the Air Force sent us?

35:40.080 --> 35:42.800
We're fuelling them as we speak. We can leave in 10 minutes.

35:42.800 --> 35:44.900
We'll do anything to find out where Lieutenant Yoon is...

35:44.900 --> 35:46.190
We don't have time to waste on

35:46.190 --> 35:47.090
a lieutenant on duty.

35:47.090 --> 35:48.740
I noticed that Seo Dae Young's name

35:49.230 --> 35:51.260
isn't on the list of the dispatch team.

35:51.260 --> 35:52.410
Put him on the team.

35:53.410 --> 35:55.530
He's already volunteered for the position

35:55.850 --> 35:57.520
and is standing by with the team.

35:59.330 --> 36:00.420
Is the car ready?

36:00.420 --> 36:01.330
Yes, sir!

36:14.500 --> 36:16.340
I told you that I couldn't let you do that.

36:16.810 --> 36:19.030
I was ordered to send you home safely.

36:19.030 --> 36:22.530
Just in case, get out of here while you still can.

36:22.530 --> 36:24.410
Why are you making me repeat myself?

36:24.970 --> 36:26.620
Do you want to waste time arguing with me?

36:26.620 --> 36:27.740
We'll take full responsibility. Take us back to the Medical Zone.

36:27.740 --> 36:28.980
No. You have to leave now.

36:28.980 --> 36:32.890
I was ordered to...

36:32.890 --> 36:34.850
I'm in charge of the medical services team.

36:34.850 --> 36:36.400
There was an earthquake

36:36.400 --> 36:38.870
and people need us here.

36:38.870 --> 36:40.440
Besides, our team members are still there.

36:41.170 --> 36:42.620
We can't go back without them.

36:42.620 --> 36:44.360
Why are you always so defiant?

36:46.750 --> 36:49.990
I don't like you at all. Do you know that?

36:49.990 --> 36:52.580
Now I know. Let's talk about it on our way back.

36:55.910 --> 36:58.710
How about dispatching a government rescue team?

36:58.710 --> 37:02.460
Uruk is an unstable country in turmoil.

37:03.040 --> 37:05.930
It's hard to send civil servants due to regulations.

37:05.930 --> 37:09.610
If you can't do anything, that's not a solution.

37:09.610 --> 37:12.400
We don't even know if the members

37:12.450 --> 37:15.340
of the medical services team are dead or alive.

37:15.930 --> 37:19.120
I'm Lieutenant General Yoon Gil Jun, the commander.

37:19.450 --> 37:21.920
I can promise you that the main goal of the army

37:21.920 --> 37:25.190
is to save civilians, whatever the cost might be.

37:25.190 --> 37:27.580
So what are you going to do?

37:27.580 --> 37:29.760
If anyone from our medical team gets hurt...

37:33.150 --> 37:34.730
If you need money,

37:34.730 --> 37:38.190
we'll pay for it, no matter how much it is.

37:39.430 --> 37:40.920
Please get on with it.

37:40.920 --> 37:43.730
A C-17, the fastest tactical aircraft

37:43.730 --> 37:45.770
will be taking off from Suwon Airfield at 01:00

37:45.770 --> 37:48.590
a half hour from now.

37:48.590 --> 37:50.220
We're sending the best of the best

37:50.220 --> 37:52.070
members of the Special Warfare Command.

37:52.070 --> 37:55.070
They’re the most experienced warriors.

38:00.070 --> 38:01.610
You're still on leave.

38:04.070 --> 38:05.710
I'm doing what I have to do

38:07.350 --> 38:08.920
But you still can admire me.

38:27.040 --> 38:30.340
Ja Ae! Ha Ja Ae! Where are you?

38:30.340 --> 38:31.580
Ha Ja Ae! Ha Ja Ae!

38:32.410 --> 38:33.380
Ha Ja Ae!

38:33.380 --> 38:35.970
Keep it down! I'm right here!

38:36.540 --> 38:38.860
Why did you come back? I thought you'd left.

38:40.080 --> 38:41.390
Thank god you're okay.

38:42.840 --> 38:44.080
I'm glad you're okay.

38:44.080 --> 38:46.370
Are you okay? Is anyone hurt?

38:46.370 --> 38:49.460
It was pretty bad, but everyone's okay.

38:49.460 --> 38:52.190
The phones weren't working and we couldn't reach you.

38:52.870 --> 38:54.880
I was so terrified.

38:56.440 --> 38:59.720
It's okay. Don't cry. I'm glad you're all okay.

38:59.720 --> 39:01.900
Don't go anywhere and stay here.

39:01.900 --> 39:03.330
I'll try to contact the hospital in Seoul first.

39:07.960 --> 39:09.050
What's wrong with him?

39:09.440 --> 39:12.700
It's a dislocated shoulder, but Lieutenant Yoon took care of it.

39:14.920 --> 39:16.900
It's nothing. I'm fine.

39:18.950 --> 39:20.840
The people in the barracks seem to be okay.

39:21.890 --> 39:23.300
By the way, why did you come back?

39:23.680 --> 39:24.970
Was the airport hit badly as well?

39:25.580 --> 39:27.720
Was that it? The planes can't take off?

39:27.720 --> 39:30.420
It's not that. The airport is fine.

39:30.420 --> 39:32.110
Not knowing what happened to you,

39:32.110 --> 39:33.400
we couldn't just leave.

39:33.760 --> 39:35.290
That's why we came back.

39:36.860 --> 39:38.660
Thank god.

39:38.660 --> 39:40.670
I thought I was stuck here.

39:41.020 --> 39:42.640
Medical Team! Medical Team!

39:42.640 --> 39:44.710
Lieutenant Yoon! Are you there?

39:45.390 --> 39:48.100
This is Lieutenant Yoon. What is it?

39:48.730 --> 39:52.820
This is the Haesung Power Plant. It's all collapsed.

39:53.000 --> 39:55.610
What? I can't hear you.

39:57.350 --> 39:59.020
The power plant has collapsed.

40:04.220 --> 40:05.360
Oh my!

41:09.200 --> 41:10.610
Put your uniform on

41:10.610 --> 41:11.940
so the patients can recognize you easily.

41:11.940 --> 41:13.510
You know the triage sorting, right?

41:13.510 --> 41:15.900
Green for non-emergency. Yellow for minor injuries.

41:15.900 --> 41:18.330
Red for those who need immediate care.

41:18.330 --> 41:20.980
And black for those who are impossible to treat

41:20.980 --> 41:24.130
and those who are deceased.

41:24.600 --> 41:27.060
Give up on patients with the black tags patients

41:27.060 --> 41:29.520
and move on to the ones you can save.

41:29.520 --> 41:32.210
Do we have to get your permission to dispense morphine or demerol?

41:32.210 --> 41:34.080
No. We have no time to do that.

41:34.380 --> 41:37.160
I want you to make your own decisions considering the situation

41:37.160 --> 41:39.840
and do what you think is best for the patients.

41:40.390 --> 41:41.480
Let's get started!

42:11.810 --> 42:12.810
Medical team!

42:20.060 --> 42:20.750
Are you okay?

42:20.750 --> 42:22.480
I'm okay. He's the patient.

42:23.050 --> 42:25.680
Sir! Sir! Can you hear me?

42:25.740 --> 42:28.890
He's not bleeding and he's got a pulse, but he's unconscious.

42:28.940 --> 42:30.610
It's a temporary shock.

42:30.610 --> 42:32.350
Can you supply oxygen while I put him on an IV?

42:32.350 --> 42:33.080
Yes, ma'am.

42:49.550 --> 42:50.470
Hold on for a sec.

42:56.390 --> 43:00.050
I'm the chief manager of this construction site.

43:00.050 --> 43:01.690
Have you started searching the building?

43:01.690 --> 43:03.300
Debris is still falling.

43:03.300 --> 43:04.680
Entry to the building is currently prohibited.

43:04.680 --> 43:07.390
By the way, can you tell me how many workers are on the site?

43:07.770 --> 43:09.140
I can't find Mr. Koh anywhere.

43:10.440 --> 43:12.560
Including Mr. Koh,

43:12.560 --> 43:14.870
the afternoon shift is 30...

43:14.870 --> 43:16.070
-How should I know? -Pardon?

43:16.070 --> 43:17.360
I think he's still stuck there.

43:19.980 --> 43:21.460
This is what we're going to do.

43:21.460 --> 43:24.900
I left something very important in my office, so...

43:24.900 --> 43:27.070
There's a survivor! I need help!

43:27.070 --> 43:28.920
I'm on my way!

43:28.920 --> 43:30.380
- Stay away from the site, sir. - Hey!

43:30.380 --> 43:31.360
What did I tell you?

43:31.360 --> 43:33.040
Go to my office! Hey!

43:34.460 --> 43:36.100
Ms. Ha! Ms. Ha!

43:38.920 --> 43:40.460
It's upper GI bleeding.

43:41.950 --> 43:43.660
Dr. Lee! Dr. Lee!

44:04.810 --> 44:06.730
Geez. This sucks!

44:07.790 --> 44:11.440
Hey! I'm down here! Is anyone there?

44:12.400 --> 44:16.940
Hey! I'm over here. I'm dying here.

44:16.940 --> 44:18.040
Boss!

44:20.060 --> 44:22.960
It's Bayu! I'm Bayu!

44:23.650 --> 44:26.590
Quick! Quick! Help me!

44:28.460 --> 44:30.970
Who? Bayu?

44:31.390 --> 44:35.600
Bayu, don:23,120

44:36.360 --> 44:41.720
Bayu's in pain. Bayu's dying.

44:41.720 --> 44:45.190
Are you hurt? Are you in pain?

44:45.580 --> 44:47.760
Oh my! I can't move at all.

44:48.310 --> 44:53.040
Anyway, hang in there. Okay?

44:56.780 --> 45:02.790
I'm over here.

45:03.480 --> 45:06.260
Is anyone out there? Please help us.

45:14.620 --> 45:17.260
I'll take care of him. Can you go over there?

45:20.620 --> 45:21.970
Dr. Lee's there.

45:24.500 --> 45:25.900
No.

45:25.900 --> 45:27.680
I'll take care of him. Go help him.

45:34.540 --> 45:36.540
How is he?

45:36.960 --> 45:38.800
I've got a pulse.

45:38.800 --> 45:40.680
I think I can save him.

45:58.320 --> 46:00.600
His pulse is pretty weak.

46:00.600 --> 46:02.490
It's cardiac arrest due to heavy bleeding.

46:03.730 --> 46:06.940
It's unfortunate, but he's dead.

46:06.940 --> 46:12.080
No. I can do this. I can save him!

46:14.990 --> 46:16.130
Stop.

46:19.550 --> 46:22.070
Time of death, local Uruk time...

46:22.070 --> 46:23.000
Stop!

46:24.960 --> 46:27.660
Hold on! He was fine.

46:28.420 --> 46:29.750
He was okay.

46:31.440 --> 46:34.490
He had no stomachache, so I tagged him as yellow.

46:35.530 --> 46:37.570
I tagged him yellow.

46:40.850 --> 46:41.950
Pull yourself together

46:42.920 --> 46:44.280
and don't deny the situation!

46:44.800 --> 46:45.870
Not now!

46:46.370 --> 46:47.370
Stop acting like a child

46:48.210 --> 46:49.520
and be a doctor!

46:52.810 --> 46:57.240
What kind of doctor am I?

46:59.670 --> 47:01.310
I can't even sort patients correctly.

47:05.830 --> 47:07.090
I'm not a doctor.

47:07.720 --> 47:09.560
You're a doctor and we need you now more than ever.

47:10.540 --> 47:14.110
Because you're a doctor.

47:14.110 --> 47:15.980
Call the death of your own patient

47:15.980 --> 47:17.760
and move on to another patient.

47:18.260 --> 47:20.400
Focus on the patients you can save.

47:20.400 --> 47:22.270
Can't you hear the screaming patients in pain?

47:47.740 --> 47:49.800
Please, Lee Chi Hoon!

48:04.440 --> 48:10.350
Time of death. Uruk local time...

48:15.560 --> 48:17.460
3:40 p.m.

48:41.240 --> 48:42.510
Take care.

49:02.860 --> 49:05.280
Hey, Kang Mo Yeon! Are you okay?

49:06.540 --> 49:08.770
Please contact me. Please.

49:10.210 --> 49:14.360
I bought some wine. Come and drink it with me.

49:22.690 --> 49:27.030
As a doctor who's in the medical profession

49:27.610 --> 49:30.090
I solemnly swear that

49:30.090 --> 49:32.820
I'll devote my life to serving human beings.

49:32.820 --> 49:34.900
Medical team! Medical team!

49:36.290 --> 49:37.730
Sir! It's an emergency!

49:37.730 --> 49:43.150
I will put the health and safety of my patients first.

49:45.340 --> 49:52.520
Regardless of their race, religion, nationality or social status

49:53.050 --> 49:56.700
I'll carry out my duties to my patients.

49:59.390 --> 50:03.040
One, two!

50:04.520 --> 50:06.760
Even under threat,

50:07.660 --> 50:09.490
I'll use my knowledge

50:09.490 --> 50:11.710
for humane reasons.

50:21.830 --> 50:23.960
I'm glad it's not too serious.

50:34.010 --> 50:36.320
What? Is there a problem?

50:50.000 --> 50:52.500
I'm taking this oath

50:53.710 --> 50:56.330
of my own free will

50:56.330 --> 50:59.790
and will honor myself while keeping it.

51:10.910 --> 51:13.130
A survivor? Should I wake the doctors up?

53:07.440 --> 53:09.750
Please help me. My colleague hurts.

53:25.210 --> 53:27.190
Attention!

53:28.640 --> 53:31.070
Salute to Captain!

53:31.540 --> 53:32.980
Sir!

53:34.960 --> 53:35.780
Okay!

53:49.240 --> 53:50.290
I'm glad to see you again.

53:52.270 --> 53:53.360
Is anyone hurt?

53:53.360 --> 53:54.470
No, sir!

53:56.440 --> 53:57.640
Good.

53:58.080 --> 53:59.530
I was briefed on my way here.

53:59.530 --> 54:01.220
We can skip that.

54:01.910 --> 54:06.350
Let's start the rescue mission in the building.

54:07.750 --> 54:09.130
Is there anyone who wants out?

54:09.130 --> 54:10.480
No, sir!

54:12.620 --> 54:13.490
Good.

54:15.800 --> 54:18.010
Remember this one thing.

54:19.770 --> 54:21.470
Don't get hurt.

54:22.380 --> 54:23.740
If one of us gets hurt,

54:23.740 --> 54:27.320
we can't save people who are waiting for our help.

54:28.140 --> 54:29.200
Do you understand?

54:29.200 --> 54:30.750
Yes, sir!

54:31.090 --> 54:33.970
Dismissed. Get to work.

54:34.090 --> 54:35.220
Yes, sir!

55:01.940 --> 55:03.140
I'm glad you're okay.

55:04.000 --> 55:08.300
I was worried about you. Excuse me.

55:09.850 --> 55:11.010
Sergeant Seo Dae Young!

55:18.090 --> 55:19.560
Don't get injured.

55:20.330 --> 55:21.680
That's an order.

55:22.650 --> 55:24.770
Keep yourself safe at all costs.

55:25.180 --> 55:26.660
Do you understand?

56:51.370 --> 56:52.900
I hope that you'd be okay.

56:59.350 --> 57:00.790
I regretted all along

57:02.570 --> 57:04.710
not seeing you before I left.

57:06.560 --> 57:07.950
I won't be able to be with you.

57:09.310 --> 57:10.390
Please

57:13.340 --> 57:14.490
take care of yourself.

57:15.130 --> 57:16.800
You too, Captain.

58:37.410 --> 58:40.860
Next Episode

58:40.860 --> 58:42.300
Call your father.

58:42.670 --> 58:44.100
He’s been worried about you.

58:44.400 --> 58:45.880
What about you?

58:45.880 --> 58:48.550
How would you have felt if something had happened to me?

58:48.550 --> 58:52.430
Crawling under the concrete.

58:52.430 --> 58:54.370
I guess he doesn't want to live anymore.

58:54.370 --> 58:55.510
I'm going in. Give me a radio!

58:55.510 --> 58:56.690
I'll come with you.

58:57.780 --> 59:00.150
Aftershock! Everyone! Get out of here!

59:00.600 --> 59:02.220
What's that noise? It's coming from the power plant.

59:02.220 --> 59:03.240
Go check that.

59:03.240 --> 59:04.810
Situation Room! Situation Room!

59:04.810 --> 59:07.530
Shi Jin! Shi Jin!

59:07.530 --> 59:08.670
Go get him right now!

59:08.670 --> 59:10.780
The foundation is unstable. If it collapses...

59:11.640 --> 59:14.790
I won't be able to stop you, will I?

59:15.330 --> 59:18.200
Quick! It's collapsing!

59:19.010 --> 59:20.080
The radio is off.

59:20.080 --> 59:21.630
Is anyone there?

59:22.120 --> 59:24.760
Someone's dead.
